## Question 2: Class Diagram

### Core Classes

```java
// Main Domain Classes
class Turnaround {
    - String turnaroundId
    - Flight flight
    - Status status // landed, in-progress, ready-for-pushback
    - List<Task> tasks
    - LoadSheet loadSheet
    - Date startTime
    - Date expectedCompletionTime
}

class Flight {
    - String flightNumber
    - Aircraft aircraft
    - Airline airline
    - Date scheduledArrival
    - Date actualArrival
}

class Aircraft {
    - String aircraftId
    - AircraftModel model
    - Airline airline
}

class AircraftModel {
    - String modelName
    - AircraftType type // wide-body, narrow-body, regional
}

class Airline {
    - String airlineId
    - String name
    - List<ServiceTemplate> templates
}

class ServiceTemplate {
    - String templateId
    - AircraftModel aircraftModel
    - Airline airline
    - List<TemplateTask> requiredTasks
}

class TemplateTask {
    - TaskType taskType
    - int standardDuration
    - List<TaskType> dependencies
}

class Task {
    - String taskId
    - TaskType type
    - Status status // assigned, arrived, started, paused, completed
    - Turnaround turnaround
    - CrewTeam assignedCrew
    - Equipment assignedEquipment
    - Date startTime
    - Date completionTime
    - List<Task> dependencies
}

enum TaskType {
    CABIN_CLEANING,
    WATER_REFILL,
    REFUELING,
    BAGGAGE_UNLOADING,
    CATERING_LOADING,
    PASSENGER_BOARDING,
    // ... other task types
}

class CrewTeam {
    - String teamId
    - List<CrewMember> members
    - List<Certification> certifications
}

class CrewMember {
    - String memberId
    - String name
    - List<Certification> certifications
    - List<Task> assignedTasks
}

enum Certification {
    HAZMAT,
    REFUELING,
    // ... other certifications
}

class Equipment {
    - String equipmentId
    - EquipmentType type
    - Status status // available, in-use, under-maintenance
    - List<AircraftType> compatibleAircraftTypes
}

enum EquipmentType {
    FUEL_TRUCK,
    BELT_LOADER,
    STAIR_CAR,
    // ... other equipment types
}

class LoadSheet {
    - String loadSheetId
    - Turnaround turnaround
    - double totalWeight
    - double fuelAmount
    - CargoSummary cargo
    - boolean isSigned
    - Date signedDate
    - String pilotSignature
}

class IncidentReport {
    - String incidentId
    - IncidentType type
    - String description
    - Date reportedDate
    - CrewMember reportedBy
    - Status status // pending, under-review, resolved
    - boolean isCritical
    - Aircraft affectedAircraft
}

enum IncidentType {
    DAMAGED_EQUIPMENT,
    FUEL_SPILL,
    SAFETY_PROTOCOL_BREACH,
    // ... other incident types
}

// User Classes
class User {
    - String userId
    - String username
    - String password
    - Role role
}

class AirlineManager extends User {
    - Airline airline
}

class GroundDispatcher extends User {
}

class CrewMemberUser extends User {
    - CrewMember crewMember
}

class Pilot extends User {
    - String licenseNumber
}

class SafetyOfficer extends User {
}

// System Classes
class TaskScheduler {
    + generateTasks(Turnaround): List<Task>
    + checkDependencies(Task): boolean
    + validateSafetyProtocols(Task): boolean
}

class NotificationService {
    + sendSafetyAlert(String message, GroundDispatcher)
    + sendAtRiskNotification(Turnaround, AirlineManager)
}

class DependencyValidator {
    + validateTaskDependencies(Task): boolean
    + checkSafetyConstraints(Task): boolean
}
```

### Relationships
- Turnaround **has many** Tasks
- Turnaround **belongs to** Flight
- Flight **has** Aircraft
- Aircraft **has** AircraftModel
- ServiceTemplate **defines** TemplateTasks
- Task **depends on** other Tasks
- Task **assigned to** CrewTeam
- Task **uses** Equipment
- CrewTeam **has many** CrewMembers
- CrewMember **has** Certifications
- Equipment **compatible with** AircraftTypes
- Turnaround **has** LoadSheet
- IncidentReport **affects** Aircraft

---

## Question 3: Sequence Diagram - Task Assignment and Execution

### Scenario: Assign and Execute a Task

```
Actor: Ground Dispatcher
Participant: System
Participant: TaskScheduler
Participant: DependencyValidator
Participant: CrewTeam
Participant: Equipment
Participant: CrewMember
Participant: NotificationService

Ground Dispatcher -> System: Review Flight Schedule
System -> Ground Dispatcher: Display Turnarounds

Ground Dispatcher -> System: Assign Crew & Equipment to Task
System -> TaskScheduler: Request Task Assignment
TaskScheduler -> DependencyValidator: Check Task Dependencies
DependencyValidator -> System: Dependencies Valid

System -> CrewTeam: Check Availability & Certifications
CrewTeam -> System: Team Available with Required Certs

System -> Equipment: Check Availability & Compatibility
Equipment -> System: Equipment Available & Compatible

System -> TaskScheduler: Assign Task
TaskScheduler -> CrewMember: Notify Task Assignment
TaskScheduler -> System: Task Assigned Successfully
System -> Ground Dispatcher: Confirmation

CrewMember -> System: View Task List (Mobile)
System -> CrewMember: Display Assigned Tasks

CrewMember -> System: Update Status: "Arrived"
System -> CrewMember: Status Updated

CrewMember -> System: Update Status: "Started"
System -> DependencyValidator: Validate Dependencies
DependencyValidator -> System: All Dependencies Completed

System -> CrewMember: Task Started

CrewMember -> System: Update Status: "Completed"
System -> TaskScheduler: Task Completed
TaskScheduler -> DependencyValidator: Check Dependent Tasks
DependencyValidator -> System: Dependent Tasks Can Now Start

System -> CrewMember: Task Marked Complete
```

---

## Question 4: Sequence Diagram - Safety Alert Scenario

### Scenario: Safety Protocol Violation Detection

```
Actor: CrewMember
Participant: System
Participant: DependencyValidator
Participant: NotificationService
Participant: Ground Dispatcher
Participant: SafetyOfficer

CrewMember -> System: Attempt to Start Passenger Boarding
System -> DependencyValidator: Check Safety Constraints
DependencyValidator -> System: Refueling in Progress - VIOLATION

System -> NotificationService: Trigger Safety Alert
NotificationService -> Ground Dispatcher: Send Safety Alert
NotificationService -> System: Log Incident

System -> CrewMember: Block Action - Safety Violation

Ground Dispatcher -> System: Review Safety Alert
System -> Ground Dispatcher: Display Violation Details

Ground Dispatcher -> System: File Incident Report
System -> SafetyOfficer: Notify Critical Incident
System -> Aircraft: Set Status to "Grounded"

SafetyOfficer -> System: Review Incident
SafetyOfficer -> System: Clear Aircraft
System -> Aircraft: Set Status to "Active"
```

